It=E2=80=99s hard to build a robot. Building the actual hardware that power=
s physical AI is resource-intensive, time-consuming and expensive. So Nvidi=
a is doing everything _but _actually_ _building them. This is a wise approa=
ch in a still-nascent market that's heavy on potential and light on product=
s. Along with reducing upfront costs and risk, by providing the foundation =
for roboticists to build robots, Nvidia is making itself a foundational par=
t of the ecosystem. Rather than competing with other physical AI hardware f=
irms, the company positions itself as the provider of a necessary service f=
or those firms to thrive. And of course, it's Nvidia. It positioned itself =
in the center of the large language model revolution, and now it=E2=80=99s =
looking to do the same for AI's next stage.

